{"履修期": "春学期後半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course&nbsp;teaches\nthe foundations of corporate finance. The covered segments are:\n\nBasics:&nbsp;Rates of Return.\n\nValuation:&nbsp;How should anyone (a manager) decide\nwhether to take or buy a project? How does financial valuation differ from\naccounting valuation? Do taxes matter?\n\nInvestments:&nbsp;An abbreviated version to cover what we\nneed in corporate finance: How should an investor choose an investment\nportfolio? Do taxes matter? What kind of opportunities does the market like?\n\nCorporate Finance:&nbsp;How can a manager finance projects? What is\na good capital structure/issuing policy? Why are markets so skeptical of\nmanagement? Do taxes matter?\n\nBasics&nbsp;and&nbsp;Investments&nbsp;overlap\nwith material covered in&nbsp;Investments.&nbsp;You might be able to\nskip Corporate Finance if you were a top student in Investments and if you have\nthe discipline to read the book by yourself—your call. However, if you plan on\na career in business (finance or consulting) or academic finance, then thorough\nknowledge of this material is of great importance. Make sure you have it.\n\nObjectives:&nbsp;\n\nGood knowledge of these subjects is\nimportant for anyone considering a career in economics, academic economics or\nfinance, consulting, investment banking, trading, and corporate management. The\nsubject matter may not be to the taste of every student, for it is by nature\ntechnical—though it is not highly mathematical.\n\nAlthough the subject is by nature\nquantitative, I place as much emphasis on common sense, on the ability to know\nhow to approach problems, and on the way of thinking, as I place on formulas\nand equations. If something appears not to make sense—here, in other classes,\nor in the real world—ask! A friendly or even funny inquiry or challenge,\nin a productive spirit, is&nbsp;always&nbsp;welcome. I am not (too)\narrogant, and I can take it as well as I can give it. Participate, please. Make\nthe class fun! (And please don't take offense to innocent but inappropriate\nremarks.)", "到達目標": "A good understanding of corporate finance that is necessary for a financial manager of a firm a manager of a bank, or a consultant.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "Investments", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "Face to face format", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<span lang=\"EN-US\" 游明朝\",serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"游明朝',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'times\" new=\"new\" roman\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:ja;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa;\"=\"roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:ja;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa;'\" style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:;\">Introduction. (Vocabulary)</span>", "Read Textbook Chapter 1. HW will be assigned in class."], "第2回": ["<span lang=\"EN-US\" 游明朝\",serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"游明朝',serif;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:'times\" new=\"new\" roman\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:ja;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa;\"=\"roman';mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:ja;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa;'\" style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:;\">Time Value of Money and NPV</span>", "Read Chapter 2.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">HW will be assigned in class.</span>"], "第3回": ["<table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"margin-left:36pt;\">\n <tbody><tr>\n  <td style=\"padding:3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt 3.0pt;\">\n